31,ronaldo ,@cristiano,Social Media,SFR,Energy,Advertising,Video Ad,2023-10-26,https://www.facebook.com/Cristiano/videos/watch-my-last-ad-for-sfr-the-experience-was-amazing-cristianoandsfr/10154008868052164/,Paid Partnership,95,positive,yes,78,"Watch my last ad for - SFR - , the experience was amazing","Hello Cristiano Ronaldo.Happy birtday to you,I wish you happy life.You are my heart.","Includes paid partnership hashtag #SFR, explicit brand mention, and a heartfelt message.  This strongly suggests a brand collaboration."
32,ronaldo ,@cristiano,Sports,Cristiano Ronaldo,Sports,Sponsorship,Brand Post,2023-03-15,https://portugoal.net/portuguese-abroad/3370-ronaldos-key-sponsorships,Brand Tag + Promotional Caption,95,positive,yes,78,Ronaldo’s Key Sponsorships - portugoal.net,"For 20 years, Cristiano Ronaldo has proved himself one of the greatest soccer players ever to step onto a field. Following his teenage years at Sporting CP in Portugal, Ronaldo has played for some of the world’s biggest clubs. As you might expect, a player who has achieved this level of success has also attracted a huge income. In 2023, he hit the jackpot when he signed for Al-Nassr at a salary of $4.1 million a week. In addition to his club wages, endorsements and sponsorships have formed a huge portion of Ronaldo’s total earnings. The world’s biggest sportswear brand is the number-one supporter of the world’s greatest striker. Though the two have been associated since Ronaldo joined Manchester in 2003, their relationship was cemented for good in 2016. Nutrition is important for athletes, so it’s only natural for a dietary supplement brand like Herbalife to work with Ronaldo. After first partnering in 2013, the striker and Herbalife launched a sports drink using Ronaldo’s personal business brand, CR7.","Strong evidence of a significant sponsorship deal, endorsements, and brand ambassadorial partnerships."
