47,ronaldo ,@cristiano,"Instagram, Facebook, Twitter, YouTube",Cristiano Ronaldo,Sports,Brand Partnership,"Social Media Posts, Media Coverage, Engagement Metrics",2021-11-01,https://www.newswhip.com/2021/11/how-cristiano-ronaldos-brand-partnerships-influence-customers/,"Case Study, Media Analysis, Engagement Data",75,positive,maybe,73,How Cristiano Ronaldo's brand partnerships influence customers,"We know that Ronaldo earns an immense amount of engagement on his own, but what does it look like when he’s tied to a brand and how does his social media status have an impact? Initially this came as a surprise due to the level of media interest he receives in general, but as we dig a bit deeper it becomes clear that engagement with Ronaldo’s brand partnerships tends to be mostly limited to his own social universe. James only saw 29 million engagements this year, and although that would normally be considered a high level of engagement, it shows how far above and beyond Ronaldo’s level of influence is on social media. In our analysis we’ve seen how content about Ronaldo can quickly erupt, but it seems that media coverage about him leans more towards his life as an athlete and brand partnerships receive engagement through his influence alone.","Strong evidence of brand partnerships with high engagement, including paid promotions, social media content, and media coverage."
48,ronaldo ,@cristiano,Instagram,Nike,Sports Apparel,Brand Collaboration,Official Campaign Page,Recent,https://www.instagram.com/reel/DTDD0ozDZNZ/,Strong,95,positive,yes,78,Cristiano Ronaldo gets his own Nike logo & brand ... - Instagram,"Nike no longer wants Cristiano, and he will create his own brand #nike #ronaldo #soccer #football #player ... [Nike Football] , [Collaboration] ,",Clear brand collaboration detected. The text explicitly states Nike no longer wants Cristiano and he will create his own brand. The hashtag #nike #ronaldo #soccer #football #player indicates a clear brand partnership.
49,ronaldo ,@cristiano,Ecommerce,Cristiano Ronaldo,Sports,Brand Promotion,Video,2019-08-01,https://www.sportquake.com/work/shopee-cristiano-ronaldo/,Case Study,95,positive,yes,78,Shopee & Cristiano Ronaldo - SportQuake,"Having enjoyed success with regional ambassador campaigns, Shopee, the south east Asian ecommerce business, worked with SportQuake to make a unique marketing move that would distinguish their key sales period, partnering with Cristiano Ronaldo to drive exposure online and turbocharge sales. Following an extensive analysis of previous ecommerce activity in football, SportQuake worked with Shopee to develop an Ambassador sponsorship strategy with global icon Cristiano Ronaldo for four key reasons:. * **Instant brand awareness** – Combining Ronaldo’s star power with the iconic ‘Go Shopee’ dance would create a ‘must see’ social moment that would be organically shared worldwide. * **Social first approach** – Shopee could own the moment through a co-ordinated brand/player social media campaign, leveraging Ronaldo’s 400m+ social following and pan-regional appeal. * **Multi-channel campaign longevity** – SportQuake helped Shopee to negotiate a bespoke set of rights that would maintain awareness throughout the brand’s key Q3 / Q4 sales period including a TVC appearance, ‘Live-Stream’ appearance & multiple player social pos.","Strong evidence of brand collaboration through Ronaldo endorsement, strategic partnership, and measurable results.  The case study details a successful campaign that directly impacts sales."
50,ronaldo ,@cristiano,Website,Cristiano Ronaldo,Sports,Sponsorship,Article,2023-10-27,https://portugoal.net/portuguese-abroad/3370-ronaldos-key-sponsorships,Case Study,95,positive,yes,78,Ronaldo's Key Sponsorships - portugoal.net,"For 20 years, Cristiano Ronaldo has proved himself one of the greatest soccer players ever to step onto a field. Following his teenage years at Sporting CP in Portugal, Ronaldo has played for some of the world’s biggest clubs. As you might expect, a player who has achieved this level of success has also attracted a huge income. In 2023, he hit the jackpot when he signed for Al-Nassr at a salary of $4.1 million a week. In addition to his club wages, endorsements and sponsorships have formed a huge portion of Ronaldo’s total earnings. The world’s biggest sportswear brand is the number-one supporter of the world’s greatest striker. Though the two have been associated since Ronaldo joined Manchester in 2003, their relationship was cemented for good in 2016. Nutrition is important for athletes, so it’s only natural for a dietary supplement brand like Herbalife to work with Ronaldo. After first partnering in 2013, the striker and Herbalife launched a sports drink using Ronaldo’s personal business brand, CR7.","Strong evidence of a major sponsorship deal with Al-Nassr, multiple endorsements, and ongoing brand partnerships.  The article details the player’s massive earnings and the widespread association with brands across various industries."
